    <!-- Translation notes -->
    <h3>Translation notes</h3>
    <p>All examples use simple numeric grades (counts, products). The paper works with graded monads indexed by a semiring, graded Freyd categories, and effect/coeffect interaction via a distributive law. For example: the graded COMP on this page multiplies two fidelity floats. In the paper, the same rule works over a preordered semiring. The composition operation may be non-commutative, and the ordering constrains subeffecting (you can always over-approximate an effect grade). The composition structure is identical. The lattice-theoretic subtleties are not.</p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 text-center text-sm text-gray-400 mt-10">
